cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GR 

The paper proposes an end-to-end learning framework for vision-based reinforcement learning problems, which involves controlling a movable object in the visual field. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.GR (Graphics). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on leveraging video prediction to disentangle the controllable object from the observation signal, which is a common problem in both machine learning and computer vision. The paper also mentions robotic arm manipulation, which suggests a potential connection to the cs.RO sub-category. Finally, the use of video games as a testbed for the proposed framework could also suggest a connection to the cs.GR sub-category.
